" {\n      \"title\": \"Hard: Nested Dictionary Value Sum\",\n      \"description\": \"Write a Python function `nested_sum` that takes as input a nested dictionary and returns the sum of all its numeric values. The dictionary can contain integers, floats, and other dictionaries (which can also be nested).\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef nested_sum(d: dict) -> Union[int, float]:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `d` (dict): A dictionary that may contain integers, floats, and other dictionaries.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all numeric values in the input dictionary.\",\n      \"code\": \"\"\"from typing import Union\ndef nested_sum(d: dict) -> Union[int, float]:\n    total = 0\n    for value in d.values():\n        if isinstance(value, dict):\n            total += nested_sum(value)\n        elif isinstance(value, (int, float)):\n            total += value\n    return total\"\"\",\n      \"tests\": [\n          'assert nested_sum({\"a\": 1, \"b\": {\"c\": 2, \"d\": 3}}) == 6',\n          'assert nested_sum({\"x\": 10, \"y\": {\"z\": -5.5, \"w\": 4.5}, \"u\": 7}) == 19.5'\n      ]\n   }"